      "content": "Garlic extract does have some anticoagulant properties, but it's not a direct substitute for warfarin. Taking a high dose of garlic extract, like 2000mg a day, can be dangerous and unpredictable. It can lead to excessive bleeding and other serious health issues. Warfarin is a carefully calibrated medication that requires regular blood tests to ensure your dosage is safe and effective. I strongly recommend sticking to your prescribed warfarin regimen and discussing any concerns with your healthcare provider. Nature has its place, but when it comes to anticoagulation, precision and safety are key.",
